1
00:00:32,265 --> 00:00:35,234
[dramatic music]

2
00:00:35,301 --> 00:00:43,265
# #

3
00:00:47,247 --> 00:00:50,216
[helicopter blades whirring]

4
00:01:01,828 --> 00:01:03,455
It's shaping up to be
a beautiful day here

5
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:05,122
in the City of Angels,

6
00:01:05,198 --> 00:01:07,792
where Republican presidential
candidate Patricia Lonsdale

7
00:01:07,867 --> 00:01:11,166
makes a quick and somewhat
less serious campaign stop

8
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:13,762
to dedicate the opening
of a recreation center

9
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:16,900
for disadvantaged youth
in the Venice area.

10
00:01:16,976 --> 00:01:19,376
This mark's the governor's
first trip to California.

11
00:01:19,446 --> 00:01:27,410
# #

12
00:01:28,221 --> 00:01:30,086
Due to an increased threat level,

13
00:01:30,156 --> 00:01:33,007
the governor's visit will be
marked by heightened security.

14
00:01:33,159 --> 00:01:36,287
Lonsdale's controversial plan
to clamp down on port security

15
00:01:36,362 --> 00:01:39,854
and the importation of illegal goods
has sparked heated debate

16
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,924
even among her own supporters.

17
00:01:42,001 --> 00:01:43,866
Detractors have called
her stance reckless

18
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:46,667
and warn of potentially dire
economic consequences

19
00:01:46,739 --> 00:01:48,104
should she be elected.

20
00:01:48,174 --> 00:01:50,802
Lonsdale has recounted that America
needs a strong leader

21
00:01:50,877 --> 00:01:52,845
who is willing to make tough decisions.

22
00:01:52,912 --> 00:01:57,315
John Downs from the BCC
reporting in Venice, California.

23
00:02:20,206 --> 00:02:23,175
[people cheering]

24
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:40,189
So did you see the game last night?

25
00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:41,227
Game?

26
00:02:41,294 --> 00:02:42,761
More like a massacre.

27
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:45,195
Hate to be the poor guy
who had his money on Atlanta.

28
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:46,232
Don't worry, John.

29
00:02:46,299 --> 00:02:47,926
I haven't welshed on a bet yet.

30
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,491
[laughs]

31
00:02:50,537 --> 00:02:51,629
Hey, where's your body armor?

32
00:02:51,704 --> 00:02:54,764
It's too hot.

33
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:56,138
Stupid.
- All clear.

34
00:02:56,209 --> 00:02:57,176
Copy.

35
00:02:57,243 --> 00:02:58,574
We're moving.

36
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:07,720
[cheers and applause]

37
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:10,820
Ladies and gentlemen,

38
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:14,485
please welcome
the Republican candidate for President,

39
00:03:14,561 --> 00:03:17,655
Governor Patricia Lonsdale.

40
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:18,924
Welcome.

41
00:03:18,998 --> 00:03:20,363
Please.

42
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:23,402
[cheers and applause]

43
00:03:31,144 --> 00:03:33,840
We will offer these kids a choice,

44
00:03:33,913 --> 00:03:37,349
an alternative
to a life behind bars.

45
00:03:37,417 --> 00:03:47,088
With your support,
I promise an unprecedented war on crime.

46
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,720
Now it's on to Washington,
and let's win this thing.

47
00:03:49,796 --> 00:03:52,765
[cheers and applause]

48
00:03:57,537 --> 00:03:58,561
I'm gonna count on your vote.

49
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:01,607
Okay, thank you, thank you.

50
00:04:13,286 --> 00:04:16,346
[gunshot]

51
00:04:16,422 --> 00:04:19,880
[explosion]

52
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:23,588
Let's go, let's go, this way!

53
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:26,632
[explosion]

54
00:04:31,004 --> 00:04:34,098
[people shouting]

55
00:04:34,173 --> 00:04:35,162
Come on!

56
00:04:48,021 --> 00:04:49,318
The alley, it's clear.

57
00:05:07,340 --> 00:05:08,807
[gunshot]

58
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:11,105
Get down.

59
00:05:11,177 --> 00:05:12,974
Hey, don't worry.

60
00:05:13,046 --> 00:05:14,274
Everything's gonna be all right.

61
00:05:14,347 --> 00:05:15,541
Thanks.

62
00:05:15,615 --> 00:05:17,549
But I think it's your friend down there
that needs your help.

63
00:05:17,617 --> 00:05:21,553
Ridley, stay with the governor.

64
00:05:21,621 --> 00:05:24,954
But you can't leave him out there.

65
00:05:25,024 --> 00:05:26,321
[gunshot]

66
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:28,257
Ridley, if you're not gonna
do something, I will.

67
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:30,956
Hey, stop it.

68
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:33,225
If they wanted to kill him,
he'd be dead already.

69
00:05:33,299 --> 00:05:35,790
They're trying to draw us out.

70
00:05:35,868 --> 00:05:37,335
Look, if we leave him out there,

71
00:05:37,403 --> 00:05:38,836
he's a dead man,
and you know it.

72
00:05:38,905 --> 00:05:40,702
Can you live with that?

73
00:05:42,775 --> 00:05:43,742
[sighs]

74
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:44,834
Okay.

75
00:05:44,911 --> 00:05:47,573
Whatever happens,
you stay put, okay?

76
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:54,119
[gunshots]

77
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,755
19, 20, and you're out, my friend.

78
00:06:02,829 --> 00:06:05,798
[gunshots]

79
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:10,496
[screams]

80
00:06:10,570 --> 00:06:11,537
Hey, Boyd.
- Ridley.

81
00:06:11,604 --> 00:06:13,037
Leave me, man.
I'm finished.

82
00:06:13,106 --> 00:06:16,166
I'm not leaving you,
'cause you still owe me money.

83
00:06:16,242 --> 00:06:17,209
Shut up.

84
00:06:17,276 --> 00:06:18,800
I'm saving your life here.

85
00:06:19,846 --> 00:06:22,815
[gunshots]

86
00:06:24,183 --> 00:06:25,445
[laughs]

87
00:06:25,518 --> 00:06:29,682
And I had the impression
I was dealing with the best.

88
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:32,452
Seems like you need a refresher course.

89
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:33,617
Now tell me,

90
00:06:33,693 --> 00:06:36,457
what's the first rule of a bodyguard?

91
00:06:36,529 --> 00:06:38,087
Fuck you.

92
00:06:38,164 --> 00:06:39,131
Wrong answer.

93
00:06:41,334 --> 00:06:42,358
Tell me again.

94
00:06:42,435 --> 00:06:47,566
What's the first rule
of a bodyguard?

95
00:06:50,676 --> 00:06:53,907
Never leave the client alone.

96
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:56,881
You remember that next time.

97
00:06:56,949 --> 00:06:58,439
[gunshots]

98
00:06:58,518 --> 00:07:02,955
[whimpering]

99
00:07:03,022 --> 00:07:05,991
[gunshots]

100
00:07:12,532 --> 00:07:15,501
[gasping]

101
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:57,609
[jumping rap music]

102
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:15,461
You sure this the place?

103
00:08:17,129 --> 00:08:19,188
This is it.

104
00:08:19,265 --> 00:08:21,825
Lovely.

105
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:28,937
You can do better than that.

106
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,737
Keep the left up.

107
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:32,107
Don't drop it.

108
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,975
Keep it up.

109
00:08:34,046 --> 00:08:39,484
Come on, put something behind
those punches.

110
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:41,042
Don't stop moving.

111
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,314
Don't stop moving.

112
00:08:42,388 --> 00:08:43,377
The minute you stop...

113
00:08:43,456 --> 00:08:44,753
Is the moment you die.

114
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:47,092
Hey, hey.

115
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:50,094
What are you doing down here?

116
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:51,129
Huh?

117
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,323
How long's it been, two years?

118
00:08:52,398 --> 00:08:54,263
Oh, try three.

119
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,994
So why didn't you
ever stop by,

120
00:08:56,068 --> 00:08:57,592
pick up the phone or something?

121
00:08:57,670 --> 00:09:00,730
I was beginning to think maybe
you didn't like me anymore.

122
00:09:00,806 --> 00:09:02,740
Oh, it's just like-
I wanted to,

123
00:09:02,808 --> 00:09:04,537
but you know how it is.

124
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:06,737
Yeah.

125
00:09:06,812 --> 00:09:08,473
You remember Ozu?

126
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:09,742
Sure.
Hi, Ozu.

127
00:09:09,815 --> 00:09:12,079
He just stepped up
as my right-hand man

128
00:09:12,151 --> 00:09:14,619
ever since your extended
leave of absence.

129
00:09:14,687 --> 00:09:18,521
Well, well,
guess it's true what they say.

130
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:21,116
Those who can, do.

131
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:24,629
Those who can't
wind up in shit holes like this.

132
00:09:24,697 --> 00:09:28,565
Still haven't lost your razor-sharp wit,
Ozu, have you?

133
00:09:28,634 --> 00:09:31,034
Looks like you're really
coming up in the world, Ridley.

134
00:09:31,103 --> 00:09:34,266
Guess this is what happens
when you lose your edge.

135
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:35,864
Ozu.

136
00:09:35,942 --> 00:09:37,569
Wait in the car.

137
00:09:40,813 --> 00:09:41,837
Sorry about that.

138
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:43,973
I don't know how you do it, Graver.

139
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,677
Huh.

140
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:49,084
Yes, he's still pissed
about the whole-you know.

141
00:09:49,155 --> 00:09:51,885
I'm sure you haven't come
all the way down here to talk about this.

142
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:55,416
No, it's not.

143
00:09:55,494 --> 00:09:57,086
I've got a potential client, John,

144
00:09:57,163 --> 00:10:00,496
big government witness.

145
00:10:00,566 --> 00:10:02,329
I need the best for this job.

146
00:10:02,401 --> 00:10:05,097
I don't do this anymore.

147
00:10:05,171 --> 00:10:07,264
This client specifically
asked for you,

148
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:09,103
knows that you're the best
in the business.

149
00:10:09,175 --> 00:10:10,574
I'm not in the business.

150
00:10:10,643 --> 00:10:11,735
You're part of the package.

151
00:10:11,811 --> 00:10:15,770
Without you, I lose the account.

152
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:20,584
All right, fine.

153
00:10:20,653 --> 00:10:23,053
I'm in way over my head here, okay?

154
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:27,149
So call this what you want,
a personal favor,

155
00:10:27,226 --> 00:10:29,319
a professional courtesy, whatever.

156
00:10:29,395 --> 00:10:33,195
Just do this one for me, John.

157
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:39,502
Look, when I walked away
from this three years ago,

158
00:10:39,572 --> 00:10:40,561
it was for keeps.

159
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,607
You don't mean that.

160
00:10:41,674 --> 00:10:43,198
I know you.

161
00:10:43,275 --> 00:10:44,264
You weren't there.

162
00:10:44,343 --> 00:10:46,903
You didn't have to watch her die.

163
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:52,508
Take a good look at yourself.

164
00:10:52,585 --> 00:10:55,520
You don't belong here.

165
00:10:55,588 --> 00:10:57,021
You're better than this.

166
00:10:57,089 --> 00:10:58,215
No, I'm not.

167
00:10:58,290 --> 00:11:00,781
I'm through with it.

168
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:03,192
[chuckles]

169
00:11:03,262 --> 00:11:05,890
You always were
one stubborn son of a bitch.

170
00:11:09,769 --> 00:11:14,638
Anyway, in case you change your mind.

171
00:11:14,707 --> 00:11:16,698
I won't.

172
00:11:16,776 --> 00:11:18,368
Nice card.

173
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:21,413
Thank you.

174
00:11:29,321 --> 00:11:32,984
Don't stop.

175
00:11:33,059 --> 00:11:36,028
Come on.

176
00:12:37,156 --> 00:12:38,817
Where are you going?

177
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:40,449
Salvitti called in sick today.

178
00:12:40,526 --> 00:12:41,754
You're joking, right?

179
00:12:41,827 --> 00:12:43,260
No, I'm not.

180
00:12:43,329 --> 00:12:45,923
So you'd rather spend your time
with a bunch of gangbangers

181
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:47,397
than with me.

182
00:12:47,466 --> 00:12:48,763
Honey, you don't understand.

183
00:12:48,834 --> 00:12:49,801
No, I understand.

184
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:51,234
I understand all right.

185
00:12:51,303 --> 00:12:55,330
I understand that John Ridley died
in the alley that day,

186
00:12:55,407 --> 00:12:57,671
because the man who came back

187
00:12:57,743 --> 00:13:00,576
isn't the man I fell in love with
five years ago.

188
00:13:00,646 --> 00:13:04,013
I don't know who you are anymore.

189
00:13:04,083 --> 00:13:05,607
You're like a stranger to me.

190
00:13:10,756 --> 00:13:12,587
When you come back,
don't expect to find me here.

191
00:13:12,658 --> 00:13:14,626
Okay.

192
00:13:14,693 --> 00:13:16,991
John, you need
to work this out for yourself.

193
00:13:17,062 --> 00:13:19,121
I will.

194
00:13:58,137 --> 00:13:59,195
John Ridley.

195
00:13:59,271 --> 00:14:00,238
I'm looking for Graver.

196
00:14:00,306 --> 00:14:02,570
Training ground.

197
00:14:02,641 --> 00:14:04,233
Thanks.

198
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:12,284
[explosions and gunfire]

199
00:14:32,471 --> 00:14:36,237
Be one step ahead of them at all times.

200
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:39,277
[shouting]

201
00:14:50,456 --> 00:14:52,515
[screaming]

202
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:53,751
Ouch.

203
00:14:56,996 --> 00:14:58,190
Well, well.

204
00:14:58,264 --> 00:15:02,291
Seems we have a genuine celebrity
joining us today.

205
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:08,398
Let's all give a warm welcome
to John Ridley.

206
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:14,878
They don't make them
like this anymore:

207
00:15:14,947 --> 00:15:19,975
washed-out fools who can't keep
their clients alive.

208
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:25,854
That's something this man
knows all about.

209
00:15:27,059 --> 00:15:28,390
Isn't that right?

210
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:31,452
You know, Ozu, if looks could kill,
I would be half dead.

211
00:15:38,170 --> 00:15:39,967
Go to hell.

212
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:41,734
Been there;
done that.

213
00:15:41,807 --> 00:15:43,172
Ozu!

214
00:15:45,244 --> 00:15:46,643
You have a class to teach, don't you?

215
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:50,977
To be continued, Ridley.

216
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:56,978
I didn't think I would be
seeing you again

217
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:58,023
for quite some time, John.

218
00:15:58,090 --> 00:16:00,024
Does that job offer still stand?

219
00:16:02,728 --> 00:16:04,059
What changed your mind?

220
00:16:05,331 --> 00:16:06,821
Let's just say I'm ready again.

221
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:09,993
Well, I can't tell you how good it is

222
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:11,627
to have you back on board, John.

223
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:14,138
Okay then.

224
00:16:14,206 --> 00:16:16,333
What say we go meet the client?

225
00:16:16,408 --> 00:16:18,376
Sounds like a plan.

226
00:16:18,444 --> 00:16:21,004
Tell me, John, how's your Spanish?

227
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,344
Probably a little rusty.

228
00:16:23,415 --> 00:16:25,679
Come on.

229
00:16:25,751 --> 00:16:28,720
[gunshots and explosions]

230
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,071
So tell me again,
why are we in Spain?

231
00:16:50,142 --> 00:16:52,007
It's not just Spain, John.

232
00:16:52,077 --> 00:16:53,408
It's Barcelona.

233
00:16:53,479 --> 00:16:56,471
Wow, somebody pinch me.

234
00:16:56,548 --> 00:16:57,674
You gonna answer my question?

235
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,980
Part of our deal with the client.

236
00:17:00,052 --> 00:17:01,019
Speaking of which...

237
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:06,654
"Lee Maxwell."

238
00:17:06,725 --> 00:17:08,522
This is all you got, no photos?

239
00:17:08,594 --> 00:17:10,027
That's it.

240
00:17:10,095 --> 00:17:11,722
Feds are playing this one
close to the vest.

241
00:17:11,797 --> 00:17:14,823
All we know is he's
a high-price contractor,

242
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:18,529
international circuit,
strictly freelance.

243
00:17:18,604 --> 00:17:19,866
So how did they finally get him?

244
00:17:19,938 --> 00:17:21,269
They didn't.

245
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:26,039
A few weeks ago, Maxwell waltzes
into the American embassy here,

246
00:17:26,111 --> 00:17:27,339
turns himself in.

247
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:30,041
Says he's ready
to name names, dates,

248
00:17:30,115 --> 00:17:32,049
the works.

249
00:17:32,117 --> 00:17:33,311
Just like that?

250
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:36,548
Just like that.

251
00:17:36,622 --> 00:17:37,714
So why Barcelona?

252
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,758
One of the conditions
for his testimony

253
00:17:39,825 --> 00:17:42,794
was that he be kept here
until his court date.

254
00:17:45,631 --> 00:17:47,997
Look, all I know is,
he testifies in three days.

255
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,865
Your job is to keep him alive that long.

256
00:17:52,204 --> 00:17:53,364
Oh, and one other thing.

257
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:55,703
Part of the deal for his testimony

258
00:17:55,774 --> 00:17:58,800
was that you be brought in
as his personal bodyguard.

259
00:17:58,877 --> 00:18:02,404
Oh, yeah.

260
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:04,711
Almost forgot.

261
00:18:04,783 --> 00:18:06,944
Got a little present for you.

262
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:08,145
Wow, more surprises?

263
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:10,620
Your guns.

264
00:18:10,689 --> 00:18:14,147
Don't get any crazy ideas
about actually using it.

265
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:15,853
This gets better and better.

266
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:35,709
Maxwell has flipped.

267
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:39,342
Obviously, this poses a grave threat
to the organization.

268
00:18:39,418 --> 00:18:43,218
So exactly what does
Maxwell have on us?

269
00:18:43,288 --> 00:18:44,448
Everything.

270
00:18:44,523 --> 00:18:46,286
One of our inside sources

271
00:18:46,358 --> 00:18:48,223
tells me he's cut a deal
with the U.S. government,

272
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:52,024
and he's scheduled to testify
before a grand jury in three days.

273
00:18:52,097 --> 00:18:54,861
We can't allow that to happen.

274
00:18:54,933 --> 00:18:58,027
This matter must be dealt with swiftly

275
00:18:58,103 --> 00:19:02,039
and with the utmost urgency.

276
00:19:07,112 --> 00:19:08,807
Lareina.

277
00:19:08,881 --> 00:19:11,645
How are things progressing
on your end?

278
00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:12,911
The wheels are in motion.

279
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:16,148
We should have closure
within 24 hours.

280
00:19:16,221 --> 00:19:18,382
I hope so, for all our sakes.

281
00:19:18,457 --> 00:19:22,826
It'll be clean, no loose ends.

282
00:19:22,895 --> 00:19:25,329
What about this new security guy
they brought in?

283
00:19:25,397 --> 00:19:28,230
Our source on the inside assures us
he won't be a problem.

284
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,234
I'm counting on it.

285
00:19:30,302 --> 00:19:32,099
Now if there's nothing further,

286
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,901
I'm sure we all have
other matters to attend to.

287
00:19:34,973 --> 00:19:35,940
Thank you, gentlemen.

288
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:37,373
Wait a minute.

289
00:19:37,442 --> 00:19:42,436
You're putting the fate
of our entire operation

290
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:43,708
in the hands of this broad?

291
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:46,781
I take it you don't approve.

292
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:48,717
No, sir, of course not.

293
00:19:48,787 --> 00:19:51,915
Since you see fit
to question my choice...

294
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:57,620
The one on the steps.

295
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:06,571
[screams]

296
00:20:20,252 --> 00:20:21,617
Sorry about your man.

297
00:20:23,322 --> 00:20:24,289
Thank you, gentlemen.

298
00:20:34,866 --> 00:20:36,527
<i>Bon dia, senyor.</i>

299
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:38,763
Hi.

300
00:20:38,837 --> 00:20:43,001
Well, this is it.

301
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,543
Well, they seem
to take good care of Mr. Maxwell.

302
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:46,635
Oh, yeah.

303
00:20:46,712 --> 00:20:49,681
He made sure of that.

304
00:20:56,855 --> 00:20:58,288
Excuse me, sir.

305
00:20:58,357 --> 00:21:00,086
May I have a word with you?
- Is there a problem?

306
00:21:00,158 --> 00:21:01,455
No, no, no.

307
00:21:01,526 --> 00:21:04,154
Well, there is Mr. Maxwell's,
or rather, should I say

308
00:21:04,229 --> 00:21:08,757
the bill of Mr. Maxwell.

309
00:21:08,834 --> 00:21:10,267
[laughs]

310
00:21:10,335 --> 00:21:15,102
Lobster, caviar, oysters,
and two cases of Cava Reserve.

311
00:21:15,173 --> 00:21:18,040
Never thought a killer could be
such a prima donna.

312
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:22,240
They tailor, shoemaker, valet,
and in-room masseur, sir,

313
00:21:22,314 --> 00:21:23,679
that will go on another bill.

314
00:21:23,749 --> 00:21:27,378
If I could just have your signature?

315
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:29,420
Sorry, you've got the wrong guy.

316
00:21:29,488 --> 00:21:31,012
Uncle Sam's picking up this one.

317
00:21:31,089 --> 00:21:34,058
Send him the bill.

318
00:21:42,701 --> 00:21:44,168
Morning.

319
00:21:44,236 --> 00:21:47,330
He's with me.

320
00:21:47,406 --> 00:21:50,170
[stirring opera music]

321
00:21:50,242 --> 00:21:51,903
Aames.

322
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:53,945
So, Graver, this him?

323
00:21:54,012 --> 00:21:56,139
Agent Franklin Aames.

324
00:21:56,214 --> 00:21:57,181
John Ridley.

325
00:21:57,249 --> 00:21:58,216
Hi.

326
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:03,113
For the record,
I think this is bullshit.

327
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:05,418
There is no way just one man's
gonna cover this guy.

328
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:06,855
I don't care how good you are.

329
00:22:06,925 --> 00:22:08,449
Nice to meet you too.

330
00:22:09,828 --> 00:22:10,886
Excuse me.

331
00:22:10,962 --> 00:22:13,487
Mr. Maxwell.

332
00:22:13,565 --> 00:22:15,192
I really hope you like this music.

333
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:17,360
He hasn't stopped
playing this shit since he got here.

334
00:22:18,637 --> 00:22:21,902
Talking about me again
behind my back, Franklin?

335
00:22:21,973 --> 00:22:25,739
Now, that's not very polite.

336
00:22:25,811 --> 00:22:29,577
And you haven't even
introduced me to our new guest.

337
00:22:29,648 --> 00:22:31,912
I'm gonna have to take this up
with your superiors.

338
00:22:31,983 --> 00:22:33,848
I'm sorry, Mr. Maxwell.

339
00:22:33,919 --> 00:22:38,083
Your, uh-
your bodyguard is here.

340
00:22:38,156 --> 00:22:39,885
Oh.

341
00:22:39,958 --> 00:22:43,189
Excellent.

342
00:22:43,261 --> 00:22:45,456
[sighs]

343
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:49,728
Let me prepare myself
for the big moment.

344
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:01,175
Holy shit.

345
00:23:04,516 --> 00:23:08,782
You mother... fucker.

346
00:23:10,122 --> 00:23:12,556
Let's all chill the hell out.

347
00:23:12,624 --> 00:23:13,591
Okay?

348
00:23:13,658 --> 00:23:16,627
[beautiful choral music]

349
00:23:20,198 --> 00:23:23,759
Well, that was exciting, huh?

350
00:23:23,835 --> 00:23:25,166
Wasn't it?

351
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:28,206
[laughs]

352
00:23:28,273 --> 00:23:32,607
Well, I think I'm gonna go clean up.

353
00:23:34,312 --> 00:23:36,644
[laughs]

354
00:23:50,662 --> 00:23:53,722
Look, I'm sorry it had
to go down this way,

355
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:54,959
but my hands were tied.

356
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:57,797
I promised Maxwell
I wouldn't say anything.

357
00:24:00,372 --> 00:24:02,806
You've got every right in the world
to want to kill him.

358
00:24:02,874 --> 00:24:03,863
I don't blame you.

359
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:04,909
But face it.

360
00:24:04,976 --> 00:24:11,905
That's not gonna happen, not now,
not with the feds involved.

361
00:24:11,983 --> 00:24:15,077
He knows all the names and faces
of the criminal underworld,

362
00:24:15,153 --> 00:24:19,021
not to mention the present government
who have used his services for years.

363
00:24:19,090 --> 00:24:22,719
Look, I don't care
what I have to do

364
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,193
or who I have to go through.

365
00:24:24,262 --> 00:24:26,492
This guy is a dead man.

366
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:27,657
Understand?

367
00:24:27,732 --> 00:24:29,256
I have no problem with that.

368
00:24:29,334 --> 00:24:30,858
Excuse me?

369
00:24:30,936 --> 00:24:32,426
You're absolutely right.

370
00:24:32,504 --> 00:24:34,563
The son of a bitch deserves to die.

371
00:24:34,639 --> 00:24:36,266
But not just yet.

372
00:24:36,341 --> 00:24:39,401
All you have to do is keep him alive
for three more days.

373
00:24:40,579 --> 00:24:42,308
Three days,

374
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:44,541
till he testifies.

375
00:24:44,616 --> 00:24:46,208
After that, frankly,

376
00:24:46,284 --> 00:24:50,015
nobody's gonna give a good goddamn
what happens to him.

377
00:24:50,088 --> 00:24:52,955
Think about it, John.

378
00:24:53,024 --> 00:24:54,855
You finally got a chance
to even the score.

379
00:24:56,328 --> 00:24:58,057
I bet you lie awake at night
just thinking about

380
00:24:58,129 --> 00:25:01,394
what you'd like to do to him.

381
00:25:04,536 --> 00:25:08,495
Well, now's your chance.

382
00:25:09,774 --> 00:25:11,071
But you got to decide now.

383
00:25:11,142 --> 00:25:12,507
You don't take this job,

384
00:25:12,577 --> 00:25:14,738
you'll never see
Maxwell again, ever.

385
00:25:14,813 --> 00:25:20,877
They'll bury him so deep,
even a psychic won't be able to find him.

386
00:25:20,952 --> 00:25:22,010
Just think,

387
00:25:22,087 --> 00:25:25,215
three days from now,
he's all yours.

388
00:25:25,290 --> 00:25:29,192
Plus, you get a nice fat paycheck
on top of it.

389
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:31,627
It's win-win all the way around.

390
00:25:31,696 --> 00:25:33,061
I don't get it.

391
00:25:33,131 --> 00:25:34,098
Why me?

392
00:25:34,165 --> 00:25:35,928
What does he want with me?

393
00:25:36,001 --> 00:25:38,993
Who knows how his sick mind works?

394
00:25:39,070 --> 00:25:40,059
Just play along.

395
00:25:40,138 --> 00:25:45,508
Babysit his sorry ass for three days.

396
00:25:45,577 --> 00:25:47,306
Then...

397
00:25:49,414 --> 00:25:53,441
So what's it gonna be, John?

398
00:25:53,518 --> 00:25:57,477
I need an answer.

399
00:26:08,099 --> 00:26:09,191
Everything secure?

400
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:12,236
Yeah, no thanks to your boy.

401
00:26:16,441 --> 00:26:18,409
Ridley, a word of advice.

402
00:26:18,476 --> 00:26:21,445
Now, that is government property
we got in there.

403
00:26:21,513 --> 00:26:23,208
In other words,
his ass belongs to Uncle Sam.

404
00:26:23,281 --> 00:26:25,647
You got me?

405
00:26:25,717 --> 00:26:27,309
Now, I'm gonna be right outside.

406
00:26:27,385 --> 00:26:29,717
If I hear you try anything,

407
00:26:29,788 --> 00:26:32,416
I'll be through that door faster
than you can speed-dial your mother.

408
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:34,048
Do you understand me?

409
00:26:34,125 --> 00:26:36,150
Yeah, I just didn't think
a tough guy like you

410
00:26:36,227 --> 00:26:38,491
would have a soft spot
for a piece of shit like Maxwell.

411
00:26:38,563 --> 00:26:40,531
I don't.

412
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:41,861
I'm just doing my job.

413
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:46,199
I suggest you do yours.

414
00:26:54,379 --> 00:27:00,113
So you're ready to do this?

415
00:27:00,185 --> 00:27:03,882
Yeah, let's get this
dog and pony show on the road.

416
00:27:03,955 --> 00:27:06,822
Just try not to let him get to you.

417
00:27:06,891 --> 00:27:08,688
Okay?

418
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,318
Sure.

419
00:27:11,696 --> 00:27:14,927
Our field offices
are a couple of blocks away.

420
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,558
It's a private line.

421
00:27:16,635 --> 00:27:18,000
Don't hesitate to use it.

422
00:27:18,069 --> 00:27:19,036
What's the matter?

423
00:27:19,104 --> 00:27:20,128
You don't trust me anymore?

424
00:27:22,340 --> 00:27:23,307
[chuckles]

425
00:27:24,743 --> 00:27:29,703
Just protecting my investment.

426
00:27:29,781 --> 00:27:34,809
Remember, three days.

427
00:27:44,362 --> 00:27:47,195
They say crime doesn't pay.

428
00:27:51,436 --> 00:27:53,233
Ridley.

429
00:27:53,304 --> 00:27:54,430
It's good to see you again.

430
00:27:57,308 --> 00:27:59,071
But where are my manners, right?

431
00:28:00,478 --> 00:28:01,467
Let me offer you something.

432
00:28:01,546 --> 00:28:05,812
Would you like something to drink,
a little local beer?

433
00:28:05,884 --> 00:28:08,910
Some wine?

434
00:28:08,987 --> 00:28:10,079
A little scotch maybe?

435
00:28:10,155 --> 00:28:11,122
You like that?

436
00:28:11,189 --> 00:28:12,156
Oh, wait.

437
00:28:12,223 --> 00:28:13,190
Am I bad?

438
00:28:13,258 --> 00:28:14,350
[chuckles]

439
00:28:14,426 --> 00:28:16,121
Am I bad?

440
00:28:16,194 --> 00:28:17,422
You can't drink, right?

441
00:28:17,495 --> 00:28:20,760
That's right, no drinking on the job.

442
00:28:20,832 --> 00:28:23,027
It dulls your reflexes.

443
00:28:23,101 --> 00:28:24,068
Yeah.

444
00:28:24,135 --> 00:28:25,796
[chuckles]

445
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:28,737
Come on, you know,
you got to relax, Ridley.

446
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:31,332
You're way too uptight.

447
00:28:31,409 --> 00:28:34,037
Maybe you can't drink, but I can.

448
00:28:34,112 --> 00:28:40,745
So how about
you share one with me, no?

449
00:28:43,688 --> 00:28:46,350
Cheers.

450
00:28:46,424 --> 00:28:49,359
Mm, it's nice.

451
00:28:49,427 --> 00:28:54,524
Uh, something to eat maybe,
like a little surf and turf,

452
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:55,793
a little paella?

453
00:28:55,867 --> 00:28:58,461
I could have the room service
set it up for you.

454
00:28:58,536 --> 00:29:02,939
Here we go,
some nice Cuban cigars.

455
00:29:03,007 --> 00:29:05,703
How about it?

456
00:29:05,777 --> 00:29:08,268
Cuban, just for you.

457
00:29:08,346 --> 00:29:10,041
Fuck it.

458
00:29:10,115 --> 00:29:11,605
They'll kill you anyway, those things.

459
00:29:11,683 --> 00:29:14,550
[laughs]

460
00:29:14,619 --> 00:29:17,452
Stop with the silent treatment,
Ridley, huh?

461
00:29:17,522 --> 00:29:19,683
You and I,
we have a lot of catching up to do.

462
00:29:20,925 --> 00:29:21,892
Nothing?

463
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:23,484
That's it?

464
00:29:23,561 --> 00:29:25,859
Well, how about some music?

465
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,763
Here, a little Brahms, huh?

466
00:29:28,833 --> 00:29:31,301
Stravinsky,

467
00:29:31,369 --> 00:29:34,065
Vivaldi?

468
00:29:34,139 --> 00:29:35,868
Vivaldi is powerful.

469
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,807
It's like the planets, the moon, stars.

470
00:29:40,011 --> 00:29:42,479
No passion?

471
00:29:42,547 --> 00:29:44,310
You're gonna like this.

472
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:52,055
[uplifting strings music]

473
00:29:52,123 --> 00:29:53,556
# #

474
00:29:53,625 --> 00:29:54,592
That's nice.

475
00:29:54,659 --> 00:29:56,058
Feel the passion.

476
00:29:58,530 --> 00:30:00,122
[sighs]

477
00:30:00,198 --> 00:30:04,191
# #

478
00:30:04,269 --> 00:30:05,793
[music stops]

479
00:30:05,870 --> 00:30:07,701
I prefer hip-hop.

480
00:30:07,772 --> 00:30:12,300
Don't push it, Ridley.

481
00:30:12,377 --> 00:30:13,469
Don't push it.

482
00:30:28,393 --> 00:30:31,794
So, Ridley, you're not serious
about this hip-hop stuff?

483
00:30:31,863 --> 00:30:32,830
Shut up.

484
00:30:32,897 --> 00:30:34,228
Pardon me?

485
00:30:34,299 --> 00:30:35,630
I didn't catch that.

486
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:37,531
I said shut up.

487
00:30:37,602 --> 00:30:39,570
Got that?

488
00:30:41,806 --> 00:30:43,467
My God, it speaks.

489
00:30:43,541 --> 00:30:44,838
What a breakthrough.

490
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:47,207
Listen, asshole,
I'm only gonna say this once.

491
00:30:47,278 --> 00:30:49,303
Just go over there,
fix yourself another drink,

492
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:50,506
and shut the fuck up.

493
00:30:50,582 --> 00:30:53,551
[laughing]

494
00:31:06,731 --> 00:31:09,700
[coughing]

495
00:31:28,286 --> 00:31:30,083
[phone beeping]

496
00:31:30,154 --> 00:31:32,122
You have three seconds
to hang up the phone.

497
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:35,693
Okay.

498
00:31:39,764 --> 00:31:41,231
I've had enough of this game.

499
00:31:41,299 --> 00:31:43,199
Let's get it over with right now,
all right?

500
00:31:43,268 --> 00:31:46,328
'Cause that's what you want anyway,
so here's your chance.

501
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:47,871
Go ahead.
- Don't tempt me.

502
00:31:47,939 --> 00:31:49,099
You think you can wait
three whole days

503
00:31:49,173 --> 00:31:50,333
before you kill me, huh, Ridley?

504
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:51,568
Huh?

505
00:31:51,643 --> 00:31:52,905
Let's stop prolonging
the inevitable, huh?

506
00:31:52,977 --> 00:31:54,001
Come on, let's do it right now.

507
00:31:54,078 --> 00:31:56,638
I'm standing right in front of you,
'cause I'm the guy.

508
00:31:56,714 --> 00:31:58,181
I'm the guy who ruined your life,

509
00:31:58,249 --> 00:32:00,513
who killed your client,
who blew her away.

510
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:01,779
Come on, Ridley.
Let's do it.

511
00:32:01,853 --> 00:32:03,218
[screaming]

512
00:32:03,288 --> 00:32:06,257
[glass smashing]

513
00:32:10,662 --> 00:32:11,629
What the hell is going on?

514
00:32:13,498 --> 00:32:15,966
Just having
a little discussion here, right?

515
00:32:16,034 --> 00:32:18,901
Yeah.

516
00:32:18,970 --> 00:32:19,937
I'll be in my bathroom.

517
00:32:24,375 --> 00:32:26,275
What are you,
in the third grade or something?

518
00:32:26,344 --> 00:32:27,311
Grow up already.

519
00:32:27,378 --> 00:32:28,811
Graver said you're a pro.

520
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,404
Maybe you ought to start acting like one.

521
00:32:30,481 --> 00:32:32,608
Yeah, that guy just knows
how to push my buttons.

522
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:39,583
I hear that.

523
00:32:39,657 --> 00:32:41,750
Truth be told, he had me
jumping through a few hoops too.

524
00:32:43,061 --> 00:32:44,619
I got to admit,

525
00:32:44,696 --> 00:32:46,687
I came very close
to punching him out a couple of times,

526
00:32:46,764 --> 00:32:48,254
but come on.

527
00:32:48,333 --> 00:32:50,062
There is a line.

528
00:32:50,134 --> 00:32:51,499
Ridley, suck it up.

529
00:32:51,569 --> 00:32:53,833
Bite the bullet,
and when this is all over and done,

530
00:32:53,905 --> 00:32:59,036
you go take a vacation and drink heavily.

531
00:33:01,346 --> 00:33:02,313
What the fuck?

532
00:33:10,321 --> 00:33:11,845
He took the fire escape.

533
00:33:11,923 --> 00:33:14,221
He's gone.

534
00:33:16,060 --> 00:33:20,224
Check the hotel.

535
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:27,095
All teams, I want an immediate
room-to-room sweep of all floors.

536
00:33:27,171 --> 00:33:28,399
Elvis has left the building.

537
00:33:28,473 --> 00:33:30,464
I repeat, Elvis has left
the damn building.

538
00:33:35,446 --> 00:33:38,415
[tires squealing]

539
00:33:40,118 --> 00:33:41,380
<i>Capullo!</i>

540
00:34:04,642 --> 00:34:05,609
[horn honks]

541
00:34:21,793 --> 00:34:25,320
Excuse me.

542
00:34:43,114 --> 00:34:45,082
Sorry.

543
00:34:48,786 --> 00:34:50,253
Hola?

544
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:51,288
Catherine?

545
00:34:51,355 --> 00:34:52,947
