01:03:29,138 --> 01:03:32,801
How about bring the whole bottle?

1079
01:03:32,875 --> 01:03:36,276
Wow.

1080
01:03:58,067 --> 01:04:00,433
Hey, mind if I come in?

1081
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:03,472
No.

1082
01:04:07,910 --> 01:04:09,673
Who's that?

1083
01:04:09,745 --> 01:04:10,712
My father.

1084
01:04:10,780 --> 01:04:14,511
He always taught me to be strong,

1085
01:04:14,584 --> 01:04:19,521
always pushed me to try harder,
to do better, to be the best.

1086
01:04:19,589 --> 01:04:20,851
[chuckles]

1087
01:04:20,923 --> 01:04:26,623
He wanted to toughen me up
for the real world.

1088
01:04:26,696 --> 01:04:31,099
But one day, he got sick:
lymphoma.

1089
01:04:31,167 --> 01:04:35,194
And I had to watch this man who always
seemed like Superman to me

1090
01:04:35,271 --> 01:04:37,899
waste away to nothing.

1091
01:04:37,974 --> 01:04:44,641
And there was nothing
I could do about it.

1092
01:04:44,714 --> 01:04:47,376
Is he the reason you became
a bodyguard?

1093
01:04:47,450 --> 01:04:49,281
[chuckles]

1094
01:04:49,352 --> 01:04:52,116
Maybe.

1095
01:04:52,188 --> 01:04:54,986
Maybe I was just tired of being
on the wrong side.

1096
01:04:57,894 --> 01:04:59,225
Yeah.

1097
01:05:09,705 --> 01:05:11,263
Why do you still keep this thing?

1098
01:05:13,676 --> 01:05:15,541
As a reminder,

1099
01:05:15,611 --> 01:05:18,944
as a reminder of a mistake
I will never make again.

1100
01:05:23,853 --> 01:05:29,018
So, Maxwell, tell me.

1101
01:05:29,091 --> 01:05:31,025
Why did you let me live?

1102
01:05:32,762 --> 01:05:34,593
Was it another one
of your noble gestures

1103
01:05:34,664 --> 01:05:36,632
of wanting to do something good
before you die?

1104
01:05:36,699 --> 01:05:38,564
Maybe.

1105
01:05:38,634 --> 01:05:39,862
You see, in my line of work,

1106
01:05:39,936 --> 01:05:41,927
you get used to pulling
the trigger for someone else.

1107
01:05:42,004 --> 01:05:43,801
It's so anonymous.

1108
01:05:43,873 --> 01:05:45,340
Faces don't mean anything.

1109
01:05:45,408 --> 01:05:51,108
After while, you know,
you get a little dead inside.

1110
01:05:51,180 --> 01:05:56,015
So in that alleyway
when I saw you leave your client,

1111
01:05:56,085 --> 01:05:58,417
protect your friend,

1112
01:05:58,487 --> 01:06:01,854
as stupid as I thought that was,

1113
01:06:01,924 --> 01:06:03,653
there was something
very honorable in that.

1114
01:06:05,628 --> 01:06:06,595
Like I said before,

1115
01:06:06,662 --> 01:06:09,222
I can never understand how you guys
take a bullet for somebody else.

1116
01:06:09,298 --> 01:06:10,356
I could never do that.

1117
01:06:11,467 --> 01:06:16,097
But what you did-
yeah.

1118
01:06:16,172 --> 01:06:18,470
I just thought maybe you should
die in a better place

1119
01:06:18,541 --> 01:06:19,530
than some alleyway.

1120
01:06:19,608 --> 01:06:21,405
What?

1121
01:06:21,477 --> 01:06:24,446
Now I'm supposed to be
thankful for this?

1122
01:06:24,513 --> 01:06:26,845
I'm just telling you the way it is.

1123
01:06:29,852 --> 01:06:33,549
Listen, I got an idea
how we could make things right.

1124
01:06:33,622 --> 01:06:35,249
What do you mean?

1125
01:06:35,324 --> 01:06:36,450
You call Graver.

1126
01:06:36,525 --> 01:06:38,356
You tell him I'm ready
to surrender,

1127
01:06:38,427 --> 01:06:40,224
but tell him only
to him personally.

1128
01:06:40,296 --> 01:06:44,289
If you're right about Graver,
you're setting yourself up.

1129
01:06:44,367 --> 01:06:45,493
You're gonna be a dead man.

1130
01:06:45,568 --> 01:06:48,162
Yeah.

1131
01:06:48,237 --> 01:06:51,138
Don't you love the irony?

1132
01:06:51,207 --> 01:06:54,176
Make the call.

1133
01:07:02,418 --> 01:07:06,286
Shit.

1134
01:07:06,355 --> 01:07:09,085
I guess the old saying is true.

1135
01:07:09,158 --> 01:07:10,989
If you want something done right,

1136
01:07:11,060 --> 01:07:13,153
you've got to do it yourself.

1137
01:07:13,229 --> 01:07:20,362
How very true.

1138
01:07:20,436 --> 01:07:24,566
And since you seem incapable
of following through on your promises,

1139
01:07:24,640 --> 01:07:26,403
the task has fallen to me.

1140
01:07:26,475 --> 01:07:28,568
I've given Mr. Tolkin my word

1141
01:07:28,644 --> 01:07:32,444
that this matter would be resolved
once and for all.

1142
01:07:35,418 --> 01:07:36,385
All right.

1143
01:07:36,452 --> 01:07:39,717
Let's finish this, shall we?

1144
01:07:39,789 --> 01:07:43,190
You, get the men.

1145
01:07:45,294 --> 01:07:47,785
You're gonna love this.

1146
01:07:53,035 --> 01:07:56,801
[machinery whirring]

1147
01:07:56,872 --> 01:08:00,808
Just a few souvenirs
from some of our previous ops.

1148
01:08:00,876 --> 01:08:03,436
Always thought this stuff
might come in handy some day.

1149
01:08:06,715 --> 01:08:09,240
Nice, huh?

1150
01:08:09,318 --> 01:08:10,945
Let's see what we got here.

1151
01:08:11,020 --> 01:08:12,248
It's a-

1152
01:08:12,321 --> 01:08:17,020
Heckler & Koch PSG1,
650 millimeter heavy-duty barrel,

1153
01:08:17,093 --> 01:08:19,891
four grooves, right-hand twist,

1154
01:08:19,962 --> 01:08:21,657
Hendsoldt scope with illumination,

1155
01:08:21,730 --> 01:08:25,393
target-type pistol grip.

1156
01:08:25,468 --> 01:08:26,435
Nice.

1157
01:08:26,502 --> 01:08:28,766
That's what I was gonna say.

1158
01:08:35,511 --> 01:08:36,478
Let's go to work.

1159
01:09:13,449 --> 01:09:16,418
[electronic beeping]

1160
01:09:33,435 --> 01:09:35,562
Hey.

1161
01:09:35,638 --> 01:09:39,369
Just thought you might
need something to warm you up.

1162
01:09:39,441 --> 01:09:41,068
It gets pretty chilly out here.

1163
01:09:41,143 --> 01:09:42,371
Yeah.

1164
01:09:42,444 --> 01:09:44,935
I take it you spend a lot
of time at fountains.

1165
01:09:45,014 --> 01:09:50,145
Well, I do some of my best
thinking at fountains.

1166
01:09:50,219 --> 01:09:55,122
That's what I was doing;
thinking.

1167
01:09:55,191 --> 01:09:57,523
I don't know.

1168
01:09:57,593 --> 01:10:00,187
I feel all mixed up.

1169
01:10:00,262 --> 01:10:02,492
That man in there-

1170
01:10:02,565 --> 01:10:04,032
That man?

1171
01:10:04,099 --> 01:10:06,863
You mean your father?

1172
01:10:06,936 --> 01:10:12,499
Yeah, my father.

1173
01:10:12,575 --> 01:10:15,544
I still have problems saying that.

1174
01:10:20,916 --> 01:10:24,249
You can't change the past,
but you can change the way you feel.

1175
01:10:24,320 --> 01:10:27,915
It's never too late for this.

1176
01:10:27,990 --> 01:10:32,222
Maybe it's time to forgive
and move on.

1177
01:10:32,294 --> 01:10:34,387
And what about you?

1178
01:10:34,463 --> 01:10:38,297
Can you forgive him?

1179
01:10:39,702 --> 01:10:41,602
[sighs]

1180
01:10:41,670 --> 01:10:44,764
I don't know.

1181
01:10:48,644 --> 01:10:52,512
Hey.

1182
01:10:52,581 --> 01:10:53,548
Take this one here.

1183
01:10:53,616 --> 01:10:54,583
Thanks.

1184
01:10:54,650 --> 01:10:57,619
It's nice and warm.

1185
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:07,562
They're coming.

1186
01:11:07,630 --> 01:11:08,597
How many?

1187
01:11:08,664 --> 01:11:09,824
Enough to go around.

1188
01:11:09,898 --> 01:11:10,990
Rogelio, take her upstairs.

1189
01:11:11,066 --> 01:11:12,033
Get her safe.

1190
01:11:12,101 --> 01:11:15,332
Go ahead.

1191
01:11:17,473 --> 01:11:19,566
I got this from Rogelio.

1192
01:11:19,642 --> 01:11:21,041
I can never understand these things.

1193
01:11:21,110 --> 01:11:23,408
They're uncomfortable as hell.

1194
01:11:23,479 --> 01:11:29,611
But I think it's time
you got a new one, right?

1195
01:11:29,685 --> 01:11:31,846
Thank you.

1196
01:11:31,920 --> 01:11:33,012
Come on.

1197
01:11:33,088 --> 01:11:34,953
Let's go welcome them.

1198
01:11:57,046 --> 01:11:59,037
Let's get this over with quickly.

1199
01:11:59,114 --> 01:12:01,344
Let me handle this.

1200
01:12:01,417 --> 01:12:03,009
It's personal.

1201
01:12:07,656 --> 01:12:08,782
Good to see you again, John.

1202
01:12:10,059 --> 01:12:13,961
So where is he?

1203
01:12:14,029 --> 01:12:15,257
He's dead.

1204
01:12:15,331 --> 01:12:16,662
Dead?

1205
01:12:16,732 --> 01:12:17,790
Ah.

1206
01:12:17,866 --> 01:12:20,130
Guess he pissed me off
one too many times.

1207
01:12:20,202 --> 01:12:21,169
I had to kill him.

1208
01:12:21,236 --> 01:12:23,761
Why don't I believe you, John?

1209
01:12:23,839 --> 01:12:25,306
[chuckles]

1210
01:12:25,374 --> 01:12:26,341
You tell me.

1211
01:12:26,408 --> 01:12:27,375
I know you too well.

1212
01:12:27,443 --> 01:12:29,536
That's not your style.

1213
01:12:29,611 --> 01:12:35,413
You always did have
a warped sense of honor.

1214
01:12:35,484 --> 01:12:38,612
Now let's stop playing games.

1215
01:12:38,687 --> 01:12:39,915
Where the hell is he?

1216
01:12:39,988 --> 01:12:41,853
First tell me why.

1217
01:12:41,924 --> 01:12:46,384
I think you owe me that much.

1218
01:12:46,462 --> 01:12:48,453
For old time's sake, huh?

1219
01:12:48,530 --> 01:12:50,725
Sure, why not?

1220
01:12:50,799 --> 01:12:53,165
I did it for the money,

1221
01:12:53,235 --> 01:12:56,068
a lot of money.

1222
01:12:56,138 --> 01:12:59,130
That's what it's all about
in the end, isn't it?

1223
01:12:59,208 --> 01:13:01,142
Wave enough green
under someone's nose,

1224
01:13:01,210 --> 01:13:03,178
and they're liable to do anything.

1225
01:13:03,245 --> 01:13:04,678
Like sell out a friend.

1226
01:13:04,747 --> 01:13:06,942
You were the perfect scapegoat, John.

1227
01:13:07,015 --> 01:13:11,782
Who better to pin Maxwell's death on
than the man whose life he ruined?

1228
01:13:11,854 --> 01:13:13,116
Nobody would ever question it.

1229
01:13:13,188 --> 01:13:15,520
And I'd be home free.

1230
01:13:15,591 --> 01:13:17,957
But you had to play the hero.

1231
01:13:18,026 --> 01:13:23,692
Anyway, I'd love to stay here
and chat all night,

1232
01:13:23,766 --> 01:13:26,064
but I have a deadline to meet,
you understand.

1233
01:13:26,135 --> 01:13:29,832
I promise I'll make it quick,
for old time's sake.

1234
01:13:31,607 --> 01:13:36,442
Now, where is he?

1235
01:13:38,380 --> 01:13:40,405
What if I don't feel like telling you?

1236
01:13:40,482 --> 01:13:41,449
Face it, John.

1237
01:13:41,517 --> 01:13:44,077
The odds aren't in your favor.

1238
01:13:44,153 --> 01:13:47,122
Well, maybe we can help
even things up.

1239
01:13:47,189 --> 01:13:48,781
[electronic beep]

1240
01:13:48,857 --> 01:13:52,691
[explosion]

1241
01:13:52,761 --> 01:13:55,730
[gunfire]

1242
01:14:00,068 --> 01:14:03,970
[explosions]

1243
01:14:04,039 --> 01:14:07,008
[gunfire]

1244
01:14:12,548 --> 01:14:15,517
[gunfire]

1245
01:14:28,330 --> 01:14:29,991
Chase him down.

1246
01:14:30,065 --> 01:14:33,034
[gunfire]

1247
01:14:41,910 --> 01:14:44,879
[explosion]

1248
01:14:56,391 --> 01:14:59,360
[gunshots]

1249
01:15:06,468 --> 01:15:09,699
[gunshots]

1250
01:15:09,771 --> 01:15:12,740
[coughing]

1251
01:15:14,209 --> 01:15:17,110
Catherine, give me another clip.

1252
01:15:19,214 --> 01:15:20,203
Get my pills.

1253
01:15:28,323 --> 01:15:30,757
Stop, Ridley.

1254
01:15:30,826 --> 01:15:32,350
No more heroics.

1255
01:15:32,427 --> 01:15:36,193
You should have killed me
when you had the chance.

1256
01:15:36,265 --> 01:15:39,257
I'm going to leave you
with more than just a scar.

1257
01:15:51,747 --> 01:15:54,716
[grunting]

1258
01:15:57,486 --> 01:16:00,421
Oh, damn, damn.

1259
01:16:00,489 --> 01:16:03,458
[coughing]

1260
01:16:05,160 --> 01:16:06,127
Oh, damn.

1261
01:16:06,194 --> 01:16:08,128
Mr. Maxwell.

1262
01:16:13,602 --> 01:16:19,063
I'm afraid your services
will no longer be required.

1263
01:16:19,708 --> 01:16:22,108
[gunshots]

1264
01:16:27,816 --> 01:16:29,579
It's okay.

1265
01:16:29,651 --> 01:16:30,913
It's okay.

1266
01:16:30,986 --> 01:16:32,146
I had to do it.
- I know.

1267
01:16:32,220 --> 01:16:34,245
I had to.

1268
01:16:38,827 --> 01:16:41,796
[both grunting]

1269
01:17:09,257 --> 01:17:12,226
[both screaming]

1270
01:17:14,863 --> 01:17:17,696
[metallic scraping]

1271
01:17:23,772 --> 01:17:26,741
[metal clanging]

1272
01:17:43,925 --> 01:17:46,894
[gunshots]

1273
01:17:50,599 --> 01:17:51,566
[explosion]

1274
01:17:59,074 --> 01:18:02,043
[both grunting]

1275
01:18:10,118 --> 01:18:13,087
[distant gunfire]

1276
01:18:19,561 --> 01:18:21,426
[coughing]

1277
01:18:21,496 --> 01:18:22,520
Are you okay?

1278
01:18:22,597 --> 01:18:23,825
Yeah, I'm all right.
- You sure?

1279
01:18:23,899 --> 01:18:24,991
Okay.
- Let's go.

1280
01:18:25,067 --> 01:18:26,034
Maxwell.

1281
01:18:31,673 --> 01:18:33,538
You've been one colossal pain
in my ass, Maxwell.

1282
01:18:33,608 --> 01:18:34,575
Leave her alone.

1283
01:18:34,643 --> 01:18:35,610
She knows nothing.

1284
01:18:35,677 --> 01:18:37,338
True.

1285
01:18:37,412 --> 01:18:39,243
But it's not a good idea
to leave any witnesses.

1286
01:18:39,314 --> 01:18:40,713
You of all people should know that.

1287
01:18:47,589 --> 01:18:49,318
You want me, Ridley?

1288
01:18:49,391 --> 01:18:50,358
You got to go through him.

1289
01:18:50,425 --> 01:18:53,223
You prepared to do that?

1290
01:18:58,100 --> 01:19:00,261
Yeah.

1291
01:19:00,335 --> 01:19:02,929
[gunshot]

1292
01:19:08,376 --> 01:19:11,345
[gunshots]

1293
01:19:17,619 --> 01:19:19,052
Say hello to the devil.

1294
01:19:19,121 --> 01:19:21,954
[gunshot]

1295
01:19:24,092 --> 01:19:25,389
Why did you do it?

1296
01:19:25,460 --> 01:19:27,860
You shot me.

1297
01:19:27,929 --> 01:19:29,726
I don't believe it.

1298
01:19:29,798 --> 01:19:30,787
How'd you know?

1299
01:19:32,667 --> 01:19:33,634
I didn't.

1300
01:19:37,506 --> 01:19:40,475
[laughter]

1301
01:19:43,578 --> 01:19:46,547
[siren wailing]

1302
01:19:55,490 --> 01:19:57,014
Hey, Aames.

1303
01:19:57,092 --> 01:19:58,457
Glad that you could make it in time.

1304
01:19:59,895 --> 01:20:01,419
Why the hell didn't you call me sooner?

1305
01:20:04,499 --> 01:20:06,433
This guy hasn't been giving you
any trouble, has he?

1306
01:20:06,501 --> 01:20:08,025
You have no idea.

1307
01:20:10,205 --> 01:20:12,332
Didn't we have fun tonight, huh?

1308
01:20:12,407 --> 01:20:13,635
[laughs]

1309
01:20:13,708 --> 01:20:14,675
Just like the good old days, Johnny.

1310
01:20:14,743 --> 01:20:16,108
Like the good old days.

1311
01:20:16,178 --> 01:20:18,942
We got two hours to get you
on a flight back to the States.

1312
01:20:19,014 --> 01:20:20,982
I hope you're ready.

1313
01:20:22,017 --> 01:20:23,712
I'm ready as I'll ever be.

1314
01:20:32,227 --> 01:20:33,194
Thanks, Rogelio.

1315
01:20:33,261 --> 01:20:36,230
You take care, Johnny.

1316
01:21:03,992 --> 01:21:06,153
So you think
you're gonna be all right?

1317
01:21:07,762 --> 01:21:09,093
I guess.

1318
01:21:16,271 --> 01:21:19,240
[people talking at once]

1319
01:21:33,889 --> 01:21:35,083
Over here, please, sir.

1320
01:21:35,156 --> 01:21:36,646
How did it go in there?

1321
01:21:36,725 --> 01:21:38,283
It felt good to get it off my chest.

1322
01:21:38,360 --> 01:21:39,327
I'll tell you that.

1323
01:21:39,394 --> 01:21:40,759
Bye-bye, Victor.

1324
01:21:40,829 --> 01:21:42,353
Have a nice life.

1325
01:21:47,202 --> 01:21:48,601
You ready to meet your new world?

1326
01:21:48,670 --> 01:21:50,604
Bring it on.

1327
01:21:51,873 --> 01:21:53,397
Let's go.

1328
01:21:53,475 --> 01:21:56,444
[people talking at once]

1329
01:22:03,084 --> 01:22:04,278
Shit.

1330
01:22:04,352 --> 01:22:06,183
Good-bye, Ridley.

1331
01:22:06,254 --> 01:22:09,223
[gunshots]

1332
01:22:22,704 --> 01:22:24,729
[sighs]

1333
01:22:24,806 --> 01:22:27,468
Hey, how do I look, huh?

1334
01:22:27,542 --> 01:22:29,237
I got to look good
for the cameras, right?

1335
01:22:29,311 --> 01:22:31,142
You look fine, Daddy,

1336
01:22:31,212 --> 01:22:34,978
just fine.

1337
01:22:35,050 --> 01:22:36,984
Please don't try to talk.

1338
01:22:40,422 --> 01:22:41,514
Now we're even.

1339
01:23:33,041 --> 01:23:36,044
[dramatic music]

1340
01:25:36,045 --> 01:25:37,045
Subtitles by LeapinLar

